-- Manchester United Winger Nani Signs Five-Year Contract to 2018
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-09-05T15:26:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-05/manchester-united-winger-nani-signs-five-year-contract-to-2018.html
Manchester United winger Nani signed
a new five-year contract, the Premier League soccer club said on
its website.  Nani, 26, has scored 40 goals since joining United in 2007
from Sporting Lisbon. The Portuguese has won four Premier League
titles, the Champions League and two League Cups with the Red
Devils.  “Playing at United has been a fantastic experience for
me,” Nani said on the website. “When I came to the club, I
never imagined the success we have enjoyed. Training every day
with top players who want to win trophies every year is a great
motivation for me.”  The new contract runs until June 2018, United said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  